rComments: This lab required heavy memorization, having 2 PDF per week that were 30-50 pages of theory with around 50-100 terms to know and identify for quizzes. Pretty much the only thing you actually need to do for this lab, you can show up not knowing what you're doing and you'll be fine, as long as you know the list of terms she provides.

She's the coordinator for the lab portion of BIO2135. Terrible person, extremely hard quizzes that can bring you down a full letter grade. I wish the best of luck to whoever has her as a lab coordinator for this course.

She's the lab coordinator for BIO2135, and she was TERRIBLE. The lab quizzes were ridiculous and required you to basically memorize 100 pages of info/pictures in order to pass. People would be getting C's, which was a good mark! imagine that! reports were annoying but tolerable. the lab quizzes were worth 20% of the final mark, so it screwed people
